title: Wall Street Breakfast May 23: What Moved Markets This Week
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description:
This is a revamped roundtable format hosted by Nathaniel E. Baker and featuring:

Aaron Task, VP Contributor Content and co-host Seeking Alpha's Alpha Trader podcast, 

Brad Olesen, VP News

Stephen Alpher, Managing Editor News, co-host Alpha Trader

Content Segments:

Market wrap-up of the week (0:56)

Earnings highlights (3:20)

Optimism in retail seen elsewhere as well (4:58)

Seeking Alpha Content That Caught Our Eye This Week (9:05)

Aaron: These U.S. Companies Are Extremely Undervalued, Part 2, by Wolf Research; Delek US Holdings - What Icahn Knows That You Don't - Part 2, by The Energy Forum; Stocks: The Good, The Bad, And The Ugly, by James Altucher

Brad: Baidu considering delisting from Nasdaq to boost its valuation

Stephen: SelectQuote prices initial public offering and Spotify locks down Joe Rogan rights

Nathaniel: Simon Property Group: Examining Apocalyptic Assumptions For 2020 Occupancy

Does the mall have a future? Introducing the "South Park Indicator" (15:26)

Learn more about your ad choices. Visit megaphone.fm/adchoices
